527
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:27,200
I wish we could stay like this.

528
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:44,000
Good morning.

529
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:47,120
Good morning.

530
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:50,520
Are you feeling better?

531
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:57,520
I am fine. You?

532
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:01,080
I could not sleep at all because of you.

533
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:03,160
Because of me.

534
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:10,840
You are the one who shot me.

535
00:45:11,120 --> 00:45:12,520
Sorry. The one who could not shoot.

536
00:45:18,240 --> 00:45:19,760
You could not bring yourself to do it.

537
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:23,320
I did not want to be a killer.

538
00:45:25,600 --> 00:45:27,000
Of course. Of course.

539
00:45:35,800 --> 00:45:37,840
You stayed up all night because of me.

540
00:45:38,960 --> 00:45:40,040
You should sleep more.

541
00:45:40,520 --> 00:45:41,520
You must be tired.

542
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:45,720
You took care of me all night.

543
00:45:48,080 --> 00:45:49,560
I am not tired at all.

544
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:53,439
Besides, since you did
not want anyone else around,

545
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:55,800
I had no choice but to take care of you.

546
00:46:01,560 --> 00:46:02,720
I think I have a fever again.

547
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:07,280
Let me check.

548
00:46:11,200 --> 00:46:11,640
No.

549
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:13,960
You do not measure fever
like that. Do you not know?

550
00:46:14,680 --> 00:46:15,840
You have to kiss my forehead.

551
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:19,040
I can tell without kissing. Do not worry.

552
00:46:24,400 --> 00:46:25,800
You do have a slight fever.

553
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:39,000
This will help.

554
00:46:41,080 --> 00:46:42,736
If you had told me, I
would have taken a shower.

555
00:46:42,760 --> 00:46:43,760
What is this, vinegar?

556
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,840
Apple cider vinegar. It is healing.

557
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:56,080
Looks like you recovered.

558
00:46:58,560 --> 00:46:59,560
Thanks to you.

559
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:03,280
I vaguely remember.

560
00:47:05,480 --> 00:47:06,680
You were by my side all night.

561
00:47:08,560 --> 00:47:12,400
I was thinking of myself, not you.

562
00:47:12,720 --> 00:47:14,400
I told you, I did not want to be a killer.

563
00:47:16,040 --> 00:47:18,800
And then there is prison life, of course.

564
00:47:19,960 --> 00:47:21,080
Yes, yes, of course.

565
00:47:23,680 --> 00:47:25,160
What are you trying to do?

566
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:27,520
Do not play games with me.

567
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,440
I am not playing games.

568
00:47:30,360 --> 00:47:34,040
So what, are we supposed to
forget everything with jokes?

569
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:43,240
What happened, what you did, I
do not even know what is what.

570
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:46,480
I do not know who is telling
the truth and who is lying.

571
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:51,320
I am exhausted.

572
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:54,080
I am truly exhausted.

573
00:47:58,440 --> 00:48:00,160
I do not believe in your sincerity, Mercan.

574
00:48:00,960 --> 00:48:02,880
You are only deceiving yourself.

575
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:06,200
You do not believe your
father either. I know.

576
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:11,760
I have no one.

577
00:48:12,920 --> 00:48:14,440
No one I can trust.

578
00:48:16,080 --> 00:48:17,680
I am here.

579
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:21,560
Trust me.

580
00:48:22,680 --> 00:48:25,320
Deep down, you know he is lying.

581
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:27,480
And you cannot accept it.

582
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:30,360
Your anger is not toward me.

583
00:48:31,920 --> 00:48:32,920
Toward yourself.

584
00:48:36,920 --> 00:48:39,240
Last night you were not
with me because you had to be.

585
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:43,480
You were here because you wanted
to be and because you were worried.

586
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:29,440
You planted me here like a tree.

587
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:33,160
How many times did I
tell you not to come here?

588
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:34,240
Why do you not listen?

589
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:35,480
Shut up.

590
00:49:36,600 --> 00:49:37,840
What is wrong with you?

591
00:49:38,880 --> 00:49:39,880
What is it?

592
00:49:40,560 --> 00:49:42,520
You come here and challenge
me. With what nerve?

593
00:49:43,640 --> 00:49:45,400
I will cover up all your filth.

594
00:49:45,600 --> 00:49:47,200
And you will act arrogant toward me?

595
00:49:48,120 --> 00:49:49,879
Ateş must not see you here.

596
00:49:49,880 --> 00:49:53,360
He is already distant with me
because of the last incident.

597
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:58,480
I swear I would be stripped
of the company and everything.

598
00:49:58,880 --> 00:49:59,800
I would be exiled by my family.

599
00:49:59,840 --> 00:50:02,039
I do not care where you are exiled to,

600
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:03,480
or what you do.

601
00:50:09,120 --> 00:50:11,120
Someone like you always saves themselves.

602
00:50:12,560 --> 00:50:14,880
My partnership in the
company was terminated.

603
00:50:15,200 --> 00:50:16,200
I just found out.

604
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:19,680
That is exactly what I am talking about.

605
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:22,159
Everything came out. I was forced.

606
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:23,319
It had to be that way.

607
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,559
What had to be that way?

608
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:25,320
Do not shout. What had to be that way?
Do not shout.

609
00:50:25,400 --> 00:50:26,999
Look at me.

610
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:28,880
Why did you not inform me beforehand?

611
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:33,160
They noticed the clause
and terminated the contract.

612
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:35,520
There was nothing I could do.

613
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:45,040
You tried to kill the woman I love.

614
00:50:46,320 --> 00:50:47,360
And I still protected you.

615
00:50:50,400 --> 00:50:52,960
Now that my partnership is
over, I have nothing left to hide.

616
00:50:54,240 --> 00:50:55,240
Nezir?

617
00:50:57,920 --> 00:50:58,920
What does that mean?

618
00:51:00,360 --> 00:51:02,880
You understood very well what I mean, Aslı.

619
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:08,320
I no longer have a reason to
hide that you tried to kill Mercan.

620
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:11,880
Nezir, please.

621
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:13,920
I beg you, do not do this.

622
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:16,000
What will you gain from it anyway?

623
00:51:16,320 --> 00:51:17,320
Please do not tell Ateş.

624
00:51:17,400 --> 00:51:19,919
I am doing this exactly
because I gain nothing from it.

625
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:24,240
Okay. Let us calm down and think.

626
00:51:24,920 --> 00:51:26,560
Give me some time.

627
00:51:27,160 --> 00:51:29,840
Let me see what I can do for you.

628
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:31,640
Please.

629
00:51:57,240 --> 00:52:01,560
Your father killed my sibling, Eylül.

630
00:52:02,080 --> 00:52:03,200
Ateş is lying.

631
00:52:03,720 --> 00:52:05,559
My daughter, do what I told you.

632
00:52:05,560 --> 00:52:08,000
They stayed here, but we took care of them.

633
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:10,640
They came to prepare our end.

634
00:52:15,560 --> 00:52:16,560
Mercan.

635
00:52:18,520 --> 00:52:19,520
You drifted off.

636
00:52:20,160 --> 00:52:22,120
Why did you get up again?

637
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:25,800
Stop. Stop. Stop.

638
00:52:25,920 --> 00:52:28,440
Do not use your arm. I will handle it.

639
00:52:41,040 --> 00:52:42,440
You never listen.

640
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:49,400
Lie down for a bit.

641
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:52,520
I was going to bring your
breakfast to the room anyway.

642
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:55,159
No need. I will eat here.

643
00:52:55,160 --> 00:52:57,600
I did not bother.

644
00:52:58,440 --> 00:52:59,440
Çiçek prepared it.

645
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:17,280
You are really like a naughty child.

646
00:53:18,000 --> 00:53:19,760
Someone always has to watch over you.

647
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:25,680
You were delirious with fever all night.

648
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:31,000
Stop.

649
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:34,120
Stop and catch your breath.

650
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:35,320
I am fine.

651
00:53:36,400 --> 00:53:38,160
You are the one making
a small wound bigger.

652
00:53:38,760 --> 00:53:40,120
Of course I will.

653
00:53:40,680 --> 00:53:44,120
Go upstairs. I will come
shortly. You need rest.

654
00:53:46,680 --> 00:53:47,920
You rest too.

655
00:53:49,680 --> 00:53:50,680
Leave me alone.

656
00:53:53,160 --> 00:53:54,960
You do not need to pretend to protect me.

657
00:53:57,080 --> 00:53:58,840
I was part of your revenge plan.

658
00:54:00,760 --> 00:54:04,440
You made me fall in
love, and my role is over.

659
00:54:10,200 --> 00:54:13,040
I can manage my stupidity
and pain on my own.

660
00:54:14,240 --> 00:54:15,320
Leave me alone now.

661
00:54:15,800 --> 00:54:16,800
Mercan.

662
00:54:17,240 --> 00:54:18,240
Do not touch me.

663
00:55:03,480 --> 00:55:04,480
Malik.

664
00:55:21,520 --> 00:55:22,600
What is wrong with the car?

665
00:55:23,400 --> 00:55:26,879
I swear I hear a strange noise.

666
00:55:26,880 --> 00:55:28,280
I wanted to check it.

667
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:32,200
Let us drink tea and then you can do it.

668
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:35,200
Eyvallah.

669
00:55:44,120 --> 00:55:45,960
Malik, we did not get to talk much.

670
00:55:47,720 --> 00:55:52,040
Sorry for my attitude lately.

671
00:55:53,480 --> 00:55:55,520
Everything made me tense.

672
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:00,360
You are right.

673
00:56:00,800 --> 00:56:01,960
I made many mistakes too.

674
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:03,880
I am sorry as well.

675
00:56:11,320 --> 00:56:12,720
Treat my sibling well, Malik.

676
00:56:14,240 --> 00:56:15,240
Okay?

677
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:19,920
I can shout at them, scold them, get angry.

678
00:56:21,240 --> 00:56:22,440
But they are precious to me.

679
00:56:23,560 --> 00:56:24,640
They are my everything.

680
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:30,559
If you break their heart,
I will break your face.

681
00:56:30,560 --> 00:56:32,600
Okay?

682
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:34,880
Eyvallah.

683
00:56:52,360 --> 00:56:56,560
He never snapped at me or grabbed my arm.

684
00:56:57,120 --> 00:56:58,120
What happened?

685
00:56:58,400 --> 00:56:59,400
Çiçek.

686
00:56:59,760 --> 00:57:01,760
Seems like Berat won't
cause any trouble anymore.

687
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:04,280
Really?

688
00:57:07,240 --> 00:57:10,800
I think the only problem left is my family.

689
00:57:11,240 --> 00:57:13,440
I need to go talk to
them as soon as possible.

690
00:57:15,240 --> 00:57:16,560
Are you going to Egypt?

691
00:57:18,880 --> 00:57:22,840
Looks like it, my love.
These are important matters.

692
00:57:23,240 --> 00:57:24,920
They cannot be solved from afar.

693
00:57:26,320 --> 00:57:29,400
So I will go and talk
openly with my parents.

694
00:57:34,120 --> 00:57:37,439
What if they do not let you come back?

695
00:57:37,440 --> 00:57:40,520
What if they convince you to stay?

696
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:43,360
Shame on you, Çiçek.

697
00:57:47,600 --> 00:57:49,080
How can you think like that?

698
00:57:50,720 --> 00:57:52,120
I will never leave you.

699
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:55,480
Only death would part us.

700
00:57:57,040 --> 00:57:59,160
Maybe I can convince them to come here.

701
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:02,080
I want them to see you and know you.

702
00:58:04,280 --> 00:58:05,560
Maybe then they will understand.

703
00:58:06,720 --> 00:58:10,240
Why I cannot give you up.

704
00:58:29,360 --> 00:58:32,080
Good morning.

705
00:58:39,800 --> 00:58:42,240
If you are looking for
Burak, he went to get coffee.

706
00:58:44,840 --> 00:58:45,840
So?

707
00:58:47,680 --> 00:58:49,520
He is coming.

708
00:58:57,800 --> 00:58:58,800
Enjoy.

709
00:59:00,040 --> 00:59:02,400
You did not have to. I
would have gotten it myself.

710
00:59:02,880 --> 00:59:04,240
It is fine. I got it anyway.

711
00:59:20,520 --> 00:59:22,920
Something is going on with them.

712
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:26,400
What?

713
00:59:27,640 --> 00:59:29,520
You really spoiled me.

714
00:59:39,240 --> 00:59:41,439
Burak, can we talk?

715
00:59:41,440 --> 00:59:42,520
Of course.

716
00:59:44,440 --> 00:59:47,760
We have all been through terrible things.

717
00:59:48,920 --> 00:59:50,680
We were all deeply affected.

718
00:59:50,840 --> 00:59:52,880
But you were affected the most.

719
00:59:55,080 --> 00:59:57,920
Demet, honestly, I am not complaining much.

720
00:59:58,280 --> 00:59:59,280
My life changed.

721
01:00:03,240 --> 01:00:05,040
Most importantly, I gained a family.

722
01:00:05,360 --> 01:00:06,920
I gained Mercan.

723
01:00:07,520 --> 01:00:08,800
So there is no problem.

724
01:00:10,040 --> 01:00:12,560
I am glad you think that way.

725
01:00:13,560 --> 01:00:15,160
No matter what we have lived through.

726
01:00:15,720 --> 01:00:17,880
I am always here as your friend.

727
01:00:18,840 --> 01:00:20,760
Demet, you are a very good person.

728
01:00:20,880 --> 01:00:22,160
A very good friend.

729
01:00:22,640 --> 01:00:24,120
I hope you are very happy.

730
01:00:24,680 --> 01:00:26,680
Thank you. You too.

731
01:00:31,920 --> 01:00:32,920
Enough.

732
01:00:34,280 --> 01:00:34,760
Enough.

733
01:00:34,880 --> 01:00:36,239
How much longer will I stay here?

734
01:00:36,240 --> 01:00:37,760
Get me out.

735
01:00:39,120 --> 01:00:40,120
Who am I talking to?

736
01:01:05,760 --> 01:01:07,800
How does it feel to stay here?

737
01:01:12,600 --> 01:01:16,440
Lying hungry and miserable
in the cold of night?

738
01:01:18,200 --> 01:01:19,720
How much longer will you keep me here?

739
01:01:20,320 --> 01:01:22,136
What is your plan? Get
me out, for God’s sake.

740
01:01:22,160 --> 01:01:24,320
Stop. We are just getting started.

741
01:01:26,640 --> 01:01:28,640
We stayed here for 187 days.

742
01:01:30,760 --> 01:01:32,640
You cannot even endure one day?

743
01:01:34,440 --> 01:01:35,440
Is this a mountain top?

744
01:01:36,000 --> 01:01:37,920
You cannot just lock
me in here as you please.

745
01:01:38,360 --> 01:01:39,360
I can lock you in.

746
01:01:43,080 --> 01:01:44,520
You did it.

747
01:01:45,520 --> 01:01:46,520
I can do it too.

748
01:01:51,600 --> 01:01:53,000
This will not end like this, Tahir.

749
01:01:54,080 --> 01:01:55,360
What happened happened.

750
01:01:55,960 --> 01:01:57,920
Digging up the past helps no one.

751
01:01:58,640 --> 01:01:59,640
Let us sit and talk.

752
01:02:00,080 --> 01:02:02,080
You took my sibling from me.

753
01:02:02,640 --> 01:02:04,240
What am I supposed to talk to you about?

754
01:02:05,200 --> 01:02:06,760
Can you bring Eylül back to me?

755
01:02:08,280 --> 01:02:10,360
Can you ease all the pain you caused?

756
01:02:15,240 --> 01:02:17,800
The scars of torture are still on my back.

757
01:02:20,960 --> 01:02:24,679
You put me and my
sibling through hell here.

758
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:25,880
How nice.

759
01:02:26,560 --> 01:02:27,880
I made a man out of you.

760
01:02:28,240 --> 01:02:30,080
You were useless, a sniveling nobody.

761
01:02:30,640 --> 01:02:33,680
You climbed to the top
fueled by revenge against me.

762
01:02:37,440 --> 01:02:39,960
You stand here today thanks to
the belts that struck your back.

763
01:02:41,160 --> 01:02:42,160
Who were you?

764
01:02:42,240 --> 01:02:42,720
What were you to me?

765
01:02:43,080 --> 01:02:45,200
Why should I have taken
care of you and your sibling?

766
01:02:45,240 --> 01:02:47,120
Should I have fed you at my table?

767
01:02:50,640 --> 01:02:53,160
You hid the real Haydar for days.

768
01:02:54,680 --> 01:02:57,040
And you found the right path in one day.

769
01:03:06,760 --> 01:03:09,280
I showed you too much mercy.

770
01:03:19,320 --> 01:03:21,720
The belt was not enough.
I should have crippled you.

771
01:04:12,960 --> 01:04:14,320
My daughter, Mercan.

772
01:05:52,160 --> 01:05:53,360
Mercan, my daughter?

773
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:58,160
I hoped you had not gone this far.

774
01:05:59,360 --> 01:06:02,680
I kept telling myself my father could
not be this merciless, this heartless.

775
01:06:03,360 --> 01:06:05,400
Deep inside, I kept
trying to convince myself.

776
01:06:09,840 --> 01:06:15,680
But today… today I lived through the most
painful, the greatest delusion of my life.

777
01:06:27,680 --> 01:06:32,440
I heard what kind of monster
you are, from your own mouth.

778
01:06:33,280 --> 01:06:34,359
My daughter, there are
things you do not know.

779
01:06:34,360 --> 01:06:36,680
Do not touch me. Do not
ever call me my daughter.

780
01:06:38,240 --> 01:06:40,200
Because I no longer have a father like you.

781
01:06:43,360 --> 01:06:44,280
Mercan…

782
01:06:44,281 --> 01:06:45,720
Mercan, let us go.

783
01:06:45,840 --> 01:06:46,896
It is not as you think, my daughter.

784
01:06:46,920 --> 01:06:50,360
Do not. Do not say a word. I
do not want to hear anything.

785
01:06:54,360 --> 01:06:56,200
Because nothing you say…

786
01:06:56,320 --> 01:06:58,599
can justify the cruelty you
inflicted on Eylül and Tahir,

787
01:06:58,600 --> 01:07:01,680
the torture, the murder you committed.

788
01:07:12,280 --> 01:07:14,760
I am ashamed to be the
daughter of a man like you.

789
01:07:16,720 --> 01:07:20,800
And I will live my whole life
with this shame you left me.

790
01:07:25,320 --> 01:07:26,320
My daughter.

791
01:07:31,880 --> 01:07:32,880
Mercan, my daughter.

792
01:07:33,240 --> 01:07:34,240
Mercan.
Walk.

793
01:07:40,080 --> 01:07:42,640
Mercan. My daughter, do not go.

794
01:07:46,360 --> 01:07:47,880
I beg you, do not go, Mercan.

795
01:07:49,320 --> 01:07:50,040
Mercan.

796
01:07:50,160 --> 01:07:52,000
Mercan, do not go, my daughter, I beg you.

797
01:07:52,560 --> 01:07:53,560
Mercan.

798
01:08:00,760 --> 01:08:02,080
Damn it.

799
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:38,280
Mercan, stop.

800
01:08:39,920 --> 01:08:40,920
Mercan.

801
01:08:42,320 --> 01:08:43,760
Stop, Mercan. Wait for me.

802
01:08:44,160 --> 01:08:46,000
Let go of me. I do not want to see anyone.

803
01:08:48,280 --> 01:08:50,640
Was I supposed to take you in
and feed you at my own table?

804
01:08:51,120 --> 01:08:51,840
A belt was not enough.

805
01:08:51,880 --> 01:08:53,800
I should have hung you by your feet.

806
01:09:00,920 --> 01:09:02,600
Mercan, you are not well.

807
01:09:02,880 --> 01:09:03,920
Let me help you.

808
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:07,479
I do not want it. Let me go.

809
01:09:07,480 --> 01:09:11,080
Your arm is already
injured. Do not push yourself.

810
01:09:11,760 --> 01:09:13,600
Not like this. Not when
you are in this state.

811
01:09:16,600 --> 01:09:18,400
I cannot breathe anymore.

812
01:09:24,040 --> 01:09:26,200
I will always be by
your side. I promise you.

813
01:09:30,000 --> 01:09:31,640
All of you lied to me.

814
01:09:32,240 --> 01:09:33,240
All of you.

815
01:09:33,520 --> 01:09:34,560
No more lies.

816
01:09:37,480 --> 01:09:40,600
I was such a fool.

817
01:09:43,680 --> 01:09:44,840
I am so sorry.

818
01:09:45,720 --> 01:09:46,720
I am so sorry.

819
01:09:47,840 --> 01:09:49,920
I did not know what was done to you.

820
01:09:53,560 --> 01:09:54,560
I did not know.

821
01:09:58,040 --> 01:09:59,080
You are not to blame.

822
01:10:09,920 --> 01:10:11,280
I am here with you.

823
01:10:12,880 --> 01:10:14,120
I have no one.

824
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:16,000
I have no one.

825
01:10:16,640 --> 01:10:20,320
Everyone showed me different faces.

826
01:10:51,400 --> 01:10:53,240
Malik, you scared me to death.

827
01:11:00,080 --> 01:11:01,080
You seem distracted.

828
01:11:02,600 --> 01:11:04,920
Are you distracted because I am leaving?

829
01:11:07,640 --> 01:11:09,799
My love, leaving you hurts me too.

830
01:11:09,800 --> 01:11:11,199
It hurts a lot, but…

831
01:11:11,200 --> 01:11:13,360
I am doing this for our
happiness. You know that.

832
01:11:15,320 --> 01:11:16,320
I know.

833
01:11:16,520 --> 01:11:20,040
I know, but I have a bad feeling, Malik.

834
01:11:20,720 --> 01:11:21,720
Why?

835
01:11:22,480 --> 01:11:24,200
What if they do not accept me?

836
01:11:24,520 --> 01:11:25,840
That will not happen.

837
01:11:26,640 --> 01:11:28,519
Look, even Mother Binnaz
did not accept it at first.

838
01:11:28,520 --> 01:11:30,640
But then she believed in our love.

839
01:11:30,720 --> 01:11:32,040
She saw our love.

840
01:11:32,400 --> 01:11:33,520
In the end, she accepted it.

841
01:11:34,520 --> 01:11:35,600
My family will be the same.

842
01:11:35,640 --> 01:11:37,160
You will see, they will accept it.

843
01:11:37,520 --> 01:11:38,520
Will they?

844
01:11:38,840 --> 01:11:40,760
Of course they will.

845
01:11:41,240 --> 01:11:44,440
I will do more than anything
needed for them to accept it.

846
01:11:44,920 --> 01:11:45,920
I promise.

847
01:12:56,960 --> 01:12:59,320
I can guess what you feel.

848
01:13:01,800 --> 01:13:04,880
I feel as if I did all this myself.

849
01:13:06,000 --> 01:13:07,280
It hurts so much.

850
01:13:08,160 --> 01:13:09,160
So much.

851
01:13:09,240 --> 01:13:10,680
You are not to blame.

852
01:13:11,760 --> 01:13:12,960
No one chooses their family.

853
01:13:18,800 --> 01:13:21,240
But they live with the consequences.

854
01:13:21,920 --> 01:13:22,960
They bear the pain.

855
01:13:24,040 --> 01:13:25,040
You are not to blame.

856
01:13:25,280 --> 01:13:25,840
Let go.

857
01:13:26,280 --> 01:13:27,280
Let me go.

858
01:13:30,520 --> 01:13:31,000
I…

859
01:13:31,440 --> 01:13:33,800
How will I look at myself in the mirror?

860
01:13:35,160 --> 01:13:36,600
How will I look at you?

861
01:13:42,600 --> 01:13:44,680
How did I not see what was happening?

862
01:13:44,960 --> 01:13:46,000
How did I not notice?

863
01:13:46,400 --> 01:13:47,240
You were a child.

864
01:13:47,241 --> 01:13:48,440
We were children.

865
01:13:49,200 --> 01:13:50,200
Let me go.

866
01:13:50,320 --> 01:13:51,560
Please, let me go.

867
01:13:53,640 --> 01:13:54,640
I will not let go.

868
01:13:55,800 --> 01:13:58,080
Let go. Your arm is injured, please.

869
01:13:58,480 --> 01:13:59,720
Let it hurt. I will not let go.

870
01:14:00,120 --> 01:14:02,680
Even if it breaks, I will not let go.

871
01:14:14,640 --> 01:14:15,400
Cry. Do not go.

872
01:14:15,600 --> 01:14:16,600
Let it out.

873
01:14:22,600 --> 01:14:26,800
Wash the pain inside you away with tears.

874
01:15:05,800 --> 01:15:09,240
Every day another incident,
every day another disaster.

875
01:15:19,600 --> 01:15:22,480
Enjoy your meal.

876
01:15:25,200 --> 01:15:26,240
Get out of my sight.

877
01:15:29,120 --> 01:15:32,480
With all this happening, you
still sit here and eat. Enough.

878
01:15:34,520 --> 01:15:36,360
Why should I not eat?

879
01:15:38,120 --> 01:15:40,960
If you can eat after all those lies…

880
01:15:43,200 --> 01:15:44,720
then so can I.

881
01:15:52,640 --> 01:15:54,160
What are you doing?

882
01:15:56,640 --> 01:16:00,120
Do not even think about
it. You cannot handle me.

883
01:16:00,720 --> 01:16:01,680
Forget about the food.

884
01:16:01,681 --> 01:16:04,160
On a rainy day, you do
not even deserve water.

885
01:16:08,160 --> 01:16:09,640
Is this all you can do?

886
01:16:10,640 --> 01:16:12,680
Stop talking nonsense
and get out of my sight.

887
01:16:15,240 --> 01:16:18,240
Instead of blaming others for
everything, look at yourself.

888
01:16:18,920 --> 01:16:19,520
Lie down, get up, and pray…

889
01:16:19,521 --> 01:16:22,600
that Ateş did not lock you in the basement.

890
01:16:25,600 --> 01:16:28,680
If I were you, I would not
get comfortable trusting that.

891
01:16:29,560 --> 01:16:31,240
My hand will always be on your collar.

892
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,920
I will not let you see
daylight in this mansion.

893
01:16:54,160 --> 01:16:56,720
I will not let you see
daylight in this mansion.

894
01:16:58,440 --> 01:17:00,239
Everyone leaves things lying around.

895
01:17:00,240 --> 01:17:02,399
No one ever says they will put them back.

896
01:17:02,400 --> 01:17:06,000
Binnaz ends up cleaning
after everyone. God forgive us.

897
01:17:12,000 --> 01:17:14,799
Mother, I poured the tea.

898
01:17:14,800 --> 01:17:17,080
Let's drink as a mother
in law and daughter.

899
01:17:18,400 --> 01:17:20,239
My dear, I have so much work.

900
01:17:20,240 --> 01:17:22,520
But since you poured it, let us drink.

901
01:17:35,360 --> 01:17:38,720
Mother, everything happened
so suddenly, did it not?

902
01:17:39,680 --> 01:17:40,680
It did.

903
01:17:41,040 --> 01:17:43,519
You went, wore the wedding
dress, signed the marriage papers.

904
01:17:43,520 --> 01:17:45,480
We learned everything afterward.

905
01:17:46,720 --> 01:17:48,320
That is how it happened, yes.

906
01:17:50,160 --> 01:17:53,520
We could not understand it
either. One moment we were married.

907
01:17:56,360 --> 01:18:00,120
But aside from that, I never
showed you disrespect, did I?

908
01:18:00,720 --> 01:18:04,680
I always followed your
customs and traditions.

909
01:18:05,040 --> 01:18:07,200
I never refused what
you asked, did I, mother?

910
01:18:09,880 --> 01:18:15,600
Yes. That is true. Thank you, my daughter.

911
01:18:17,480 --> 01:18:21,160
Then of course I expect the same from you.

912
01:18:21,920 --> 01:18:23,880
Since you know the traditions.

913
01:18:24,200 --> 01:18:29,320
Tell me then, what is your
custom? What do you want from me?

914
01:18:33,440 --> 01:18:36,719
In our hometown, the
mother in law gives the bride

915
01:18:36,720 --> 01:18:38,680
a set of five gold coins. It is tradition.

916
01:18:41,240 --> 01:18:42,880
Are you well, mother?

917
01:18:45,600 --> 01:18:47,480
Five gold coins, huh.

918
01:18:48,120 --> 01:18:49,120
God forgive us.

919
01:18:49,440 --> 01:18:52,440
How would we ever find
five coins to give you?

920
01:18:53,320 --> 01:18:55,416
You must have mistaken us
for the people of the mansion.

921
01:18:55,440 --> 01:18:57,200
What do we even have?

922
01:18:58,040 --> 01:19:00,039
You talk about tradition,

923
01:19:00,040 --> 01:19:03,519
you never came to ask permission,
never sought our consent…

924
01:19:03,520 --> 01:19:07,480
you never came to kiss
my hand. Oh, how easy.

925
01:19:07,880 --> 01:19:11,039
Tradition when it suits you,
no tradition when it does not.

926
01:19:11,040 --> 01:19:12,680
Go on, my daughter.

927
01:19:14,920 --> 01:19:17,720
God forbid. You will get over this.

928
01:19:18,720 --> 01:19:21,080
You did not even let us drink
tea in peace for two minutes.

929
01:19:21,960 --> 01:19:22,960
God forgive us.

930
01:20:02,040 --> 01:20:03,720
Come on.

931
01:20:04,960 --> 01:20:05,960
Lie down a little.

932
01:20:27,160 --> 01:20:28,160
Stretch your legs.

933
01:20:59,120 --> 01:21:00,560
Close your eyes.

934
01:23:08,760 --> 01:23:10,239
A belt was not enough for you.

935
01:23:10,240 --> 01:23:11,840
I should have hung you by your feet.

936
01:23:31,440 --> 01:23:32,840
You…

937
01:23:34,080 --> 01:23:36,520
How did you endure so much pain?

938
01:23:49,760 --> 01:23:50,760
It was hard.

939
01:23:53,520 --> 01:24:01,520
How did you endure staying in
that mansion despite everything?

940
01:24:02,760 --> 01:24:04,040
I do not know how I endured it.

941
01:24:09,080 --> 01:24:11,400
Maybe the desire for
revenge gave me strength.

942
01:24:16,160 --> 01:24:23,720
And you. With your innocence
amid all that ugliness…

943
01:24:25,320 --> 01:24:27,080
you shone like a diamond.

944
01:24:30,760 --> 01:24:35,400
My faith in goodness
was renewed through you.

945
01:24:47,680 --> 01:24:50,280
I am so sorry for what you went through.

946
01:24:52,680 --> 01:24:53,680
So sorry.

947
01:25:02,600 --> 01:25:08,360
Believe me, I feel your
pain in my own heart.

948
01:25:14,120 --> 01:25:15,960
We cannot change the past.

949
01:25:27,520 --> 01:25:28,760
You have wounds too.

950
01:25:32,560 --> 01:25:34,400
But we can heal each other’s wounds.

951
01:25:37,160 --> 01:25:39,240
We can find healing through our love.

952
01:25:48,640 --> 01:25:51,120
Let us always hold hands, Mercan.

953
01:25:53,360 --> 01:25:54,680
Let us be companions on the road.

954
01:25:57,240 --> 01:25:59,600
And walk that road together.

955
01:27:05,720 --> 01:27:07,600
Look at the lady acting tough.

956
01:27:07,920 --> 01:27:11,440
Whatever she relies on, she will see.

957
01:27:11,920 --> 01:27:14,560
Leave the food. I will make
every breath you take bitter.

958
01:27:18,760 --> 01:27:22,040
Mother, you forgot your
phone upstairs. A message came.

959
01:27:22,600 --> 01:27:24,960
Money was transferred from
your account to another account.

960
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:29,400
You knew about it, right?

961
01:27:30,680 --> 01:27:32,360
Of course I did, my daughter.

962
01:27:36,880 --> 01:27:40,080
A friend of mine was
short on money. I sent it.

963
01:27:41,240 --> 01:27:42,240
Who is this friend?

964
01:27:43,920 --> 01:27:45,520
You do not know her, Aslı.

965
01:28:01,680 --> 01:28:02,999
That witch of a mother in law.

966
01:28:03,000 --> 01:28:04,400
She did not give me a single penny.

967
01:28:05,720 --> 01:28:07,880
But I know what to do to you and to Çiçek.

968
01:28:08,800 --> 01:28:09,800
Witch.

969
01:28:20,240 --> 01:28:21,240
My wife.

970
01:28:21,560 --> 01:28:23,040
Today…

971
01:28:25,200 --> 01:28:27,320
the day never ended. I am exhausted.

972
01:28:31,840 --> 01:28:32,840
Zehra, what happened?

973
01:28:33,640 --> 01:28:35,600
Why are you crying, my queen? Tell me.

974
01:28:37,400 --> 01:28:40,360
Your mother and Çiçek do
not want me as a bride, Berat.

975
01:28:40,840 --> 01:28:44,600
They treat me like a stranger.

976
01:28:48,040 --> 01:28:49,280
My beautiful wife.

977
01:28:49,760 --> 01:28:51,520
I cannot bear your tears.

978
01:28:54,480 --> 01:28:55,480
Do not cry.

979
01:28:56,080 --> 01:28:57,720
They can, though, Berat.

980
01:28:59,480 --> 01:29:00,800
They do not even look at my face.

981
01:29:01,840 --> 01:29:03,360
They ignore me.

982
01:29:04,440 --> 01:29:06,520
When I speak, they snap at me.

983
01:29:08,680 --> 01:29:12,600
I married to be happy,
not to be pushed around.

984
01:29:14,040 --> 01:29:15,319
Think about it, Berat.

985
01:29:15,320 --> 01:29:17,080
We do not even have a room of our own.

986
01:29:17,760 --> 01:29:18,960
What kind of marriage is this?

987
01:29:22,800 --> 01:29:25,240
Do not worry.

988
01:29:26,000 --> 01:29:27,680
I will handle it.

989
01:29:28,240 --> 01:29:29,240
Do not worry.

990
01:29:31,600 --> 01:29:33,520
I have an idea, Berat.

991
01:29:34,680 --> 01:29:35,680
Really? What is it?

992
01:29:36,720 --> 01:29:38,120
Çiçek’s room is bigger.

993
01:29:38,960 --> 01:29:41,119
Since we married first…

994
01:29:41,120 --> 01:29:44,200
would it not be more appropriate
for us to move in there?

995
01:29:50,160 --> 01:29:53,160
I do not know.

996
01:29:53,760 --> 01:29:55,960
As you said, it is now…

997
01:29:56,520 --> 01:29:57,360
Çiçek’s room.

998
01:29:57,440 --> 01:30:01,400
But you are her brother,
Berat. I am her sister in law.

999
01:30:02,120 --> 01:30:04,560
She can make that small sacrifice.

1000
01:30:05,160 --> 01:30:07,840
Look at me. I made many sacrifices.

1001
01:30:08,320 --> 01:30:12,840
I did not ask for a new house or jewelry.

1002
01:30:14,280 --> 01:30:16,240
But at least let us have a room.

1003
01:30:16,720 --> 01:30:18,680
Please, my husband.

1004
01:30:21,760 --> 01:30:24,320
All right. I will handle it.

1005
01:30:25,160 --> 01:30:26,440
Do not worry.

1006
01:30:26,720 --> 01:30:29,480
You tell me, and Berat
will fix it right away.

1007
01:30:29,520 --> 01:30:31,280
My dear husband.

1008
01:31:03,360 --> 01:31:04,800
Why are you looking at me like that?

1009
01:31:06,320 --> 01:31:08,040
Did I ever tell you that you are beautiful?

1010
01:31:11,640 --> 01:31:13,000
I think you did.

1011
01:31:19,720 --> 01:31:22,080
How long will you keep looking then?

1012
01:31:26,120 --> 01:31:27,120
Forever.

1013
01:31:42,920 --> 01:31:44,440
Shall we go out?

1014
01:31:46,760 --> 01:31:48,960
I do not want to. This is fine.

1015
01:31:51,560 --> 01:31:52,600
Shall we play chess?

1016
01:31:55,960 --> 01:31:56,960
I do not know.

1017
01:31:59,040 --> 01:32:00,040
I do not feel like it.

1018
01:32:03,200 --> 01:32:04,640
Someone is running away, I think.

1019
01:32:09,240 --> 01:32:10,480
You will wait a long time.

1020
01:32:11,600 --> 01:32:12,840
I beat you badly, by the way.

1021
01:32:13,880 --> 01:32:14,880
Really?

1022
01:32:16,240 --> 01:32:18,280
Accepted.

1023
01:32:18,600 --> 01:32:19,600
Where was the chess set?

1024
01:32:20,840 --> 01:32:23,160
Someone wants to get checkmated tonight.

1025
01:32:24,640 --> 01:32:26,240
It should be in my closet.

1026
01:32:40,680 --> 01:32:41,720
Which color? You choose.

1027
01:32:43,600 --> 01:32:44,600
Gray.

1028
01:32:51,360 --> 01:32:52,720
Loser brings the tea.

1029
01:32:54,280 --> 01:32:55,280
Deal.

1030
01:32:58,320 --> 01:32:59,320
Go ahead.

1031
01:33:33,880 --> 01:33:36,640
You made exactly the move I wanted.

1032
01:33:49,640 --> 01:33:51,360
They call this the scholar’s mate.

1033
01:33:56,120 --> 01:33:58,200
Are you sure you know how to play chess?

1034
01:33:58,960 --> 01:34:00,000
Yes. Why?

1035
01:34:00,760 --> 01:34:01,760
What do you mean why?

1036
01:34:02,040 --> 01:34:04,280
You got a brand new scholar’s mate.

1037
01:34:05,160 --> 01:34:07,480
Come on. Off to the kitchen with you.

1038
01:34:08,240 --> 01:34:09,520
Make the tea strong.

1039
01:34:10,680 --> 01:34:13,360
Do not forget crackers or snacks.

1040
01:34:13,520 --> 01:34:14,520
Wait a second.

1041
01:34:14,600 --> 01:34:15,600
This does not count.

1042
01:34:16,120 --> 01:34:18,440
You distracted me.

1043
01:34:18,600 --> 01:34:19,600
We will play again.

1044
01:34:20,640 --> 01:34:22,680
While I bring the tea, you set the pieces.

1045
01:34:22,920 --> 01:34:23,920
All right.

1046
01:34:23,960 --> 01:34:24,960
Come on.

1047
01:34:40,800 --> 01:34:41,800
I am back.

1048
01:34:41,960 --> 01:34:42,960
Take this.

1049
01:34:48,320 --> 01:34:49,560
You start this time.

1050
01:35:10,080 --> 01:35:11,200
Wait a second.

1051
01:35:12,320 --> 01:35:15,520
What did you do while I was not
looking? Did you steal a piece?

1052
01:35:16,040 --> 01:35:17,280
No. I played fair.

1053
01:35:18,840 --> 01:35:20,800
You realized you would
lose and now you complain.

1054
01:35:21,720 --> 01:35:22,720
No way.

1055
01:35:31,640 --> 01:35:32,640
Check.

1056
01:35:35,040 --> 01:35:36,040
Congratulations.

1057
01:35:37,480 --> 01:35:39,880
I told you, Ms. Mercan. I slipped earlier.

1058
01:35:40,200 --> 01:35:41,200
Be thankful.

1059
01:35:42,280 --> 01:35:44,320
That was no slip.

1060
01:35:44,800 --> 01:35:47,760
Someone who plays like this
does not get scholar’s mated.

1061
01:35:48,920 --> 01:35:50,160
You lost on purpose.

1062
01:35:51,240 --> 01:35:52,560
So I would feel better.

1063
01:36:01,320 --> 01:36:03,560
Maybe I like losing to you.

1064
01:36:51,120 --> 01:36:52,520
Good morning, Sister Binnaz.

1065
01:36:56,880 --> 01:36:57,880
Tahir.

1066
01:36:59,920 --> 01:37:01,120
My Tahir.

1067
01:37:02,400 --> 01:37:04,280
My dear.

1068
01:37:06,200 --> 01:37:08,080
How did I not recognize you?

1069
01:37:10,400 --> 01:37:13,720
I recognized you right
away. You never changed.

1070
01:37:15,400 --> 01:37:16,600
How could that be?

1071
01:37:17,400 --> 01:37:20,000
Cruel years took my youth.

1072
01:37:39,720 --> 01:37:40,720
I…

1073
01:37:41,680 --> 01:37:44,680
Back then, I could not speak
up against that cruelty…

1074
01:37:45,960 --> 01:37:47,760
my son.

1075
01:37:50,080 --> 01:37:51,320
I was so sorry.

1076
01:37:52,640 --> 01:37:54,080
It hurt me deeply, but…

1077
01:37:55,880 --> 01:37:56,960
I could not say anything.

1078
01:37:59,680 --> 01:38:02,120
I stayed silent knowingly.

1079
01:38:02,320 --> 01:38:04,720
I could do nothing.

1080
01:38:06,120 --> 01:38:07,120
Forgive me.

1081
01:38:08,960 --> 01:38:10,520
Do not blame yourself, Sister Binnaz.

1082
01:38:11,680 --> 01:38:13,240
What could you have done?

1083
01:38:16,160 --> 01:38:18,240
You were a woman with two children.

1084
01:38:20,600 --> 01:38:24,720
We saw nothing but mercy from you.

1085
01:38:29,160 --> 01:38:31,560
You secretly fed Eylül and me.

1086
01:38:35,280 --> 01:38:36,640
I do not know how to repay you.

1087
01:38:39,960 --> 01:38:44,200
Eylül… I wish Eylül were here too.

1088
01:38:45,120 --> 01:38:47,799
She was so fragile.

1089
01:38:47,800 --> 01:38:48,800
I cannot bear it.

1090
01:38:50,520 --> 01:38:53,600
She was so fragile.

1091
01:38:54,480 --> 01:38:55,480
I cannot bear it.

1092
01:38:58,840 --> 01:39:00,160
Good morning, my daughter Mercan.

1093
01:39:01,920 --> 01:39:02,920
Good morning.

1094
01:39:04,120 --> 01:39:05,120
Good morning.

1095
01:39:05,560 --> 01:39:07,920
I will prepare breakfast now.

1096
01:39:08,560 --> 01:39:09,720
No need, Sister Binnaz.

1097
01:39:16,440 --> 01:39:18,280
My wife and I are going out.

1098
01:39:19,840 --> 01:39:20,840
Where will you go?

1099
01:39:21,600 --> 01:39:22,800
Wherever we want.

1100
01:39:33,040 --> 01:39:34,520
God protect you.

1101
01:39:36,000 --> 01:39:37,480
God never separate you.

1102
01:39:38,840 --> 01:39:41,960
May our hands always be together, Insallah.

1103
01:39:46,800 --> 01:39:49,080
Oh my Eylül.

1104
01:39:51,640 --> 01:39:54,320
Where should I put these bits and pieces?

1105
01:39:55,200 --> 01:39:56,920
I will put them here. Çiçek will take them.

1106
01:39:59,920 --> 01:40:01,160
What are you doing?

1107
01:40:02,000 --> 01:40:03,040
Why do you have my things?

1108
01:40:04,000 --> 01:40:07,200
I was looking for a place to
put them. Çiçek, come help me.

1109
01:40:08,120 --> 01:40:10,800
Why are you in my room?
Who gave you permission?

1110
01:40:11,800 --> 01:40:16,080
My dear, that is no longer your room.

1111
01:40:17,120 --> 01:40:18,200
It is Berat’s and my room.

1112
01:40:19,240 --> 01:40:20,240
Why?

1113
01:40:21,160 --> 01:40:22,680
What do you mean?

1114
01:40:23,720 --> 01:40:26,519
Because we decided so.

1115
01:40:26,520 --> 01:40:29,080
We thought it would be more appropriate.

1116
01:40:29,560 --> 01:40:31,600
You could have asked me at least.

1117
01:40:32,680 --> 01:40:33,960
Oh please.

1118
01:40:34,520 --> 01:40:35,680
You have lost your minds.

1119
01:40:35,920 --> 01:40:36,920
What are you doing?

1120
01:40:37,400 --> 01:40:38,400
Move.

1121
01:40:38,480 --> 01:40:40,239
Hey, move.

1122
01:40:40,240 --> 01:40:41,480
What is happening here?

1123
01:40:42,160 --> 01:40:44,680
Mother, she took over my room.

1124
01:40:45,200 --> 01:40:47,480
Soon she will take the whole house.

1125
01:40:47,560 --> 01:40:48,720
She is dangerous.

1126
01:40:49,600 --> 01:40:51,240
My dear, let us not say took over.

1127
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:54,440
My husband and I…

1128
01:40:55,200 --> 01:40:57,880
discussed it and decided so.

1129
01:40:58,000 --> 01:40:59,000
Right, my husband?

1130
01:41:00,240 --> 01:41:01,400
Yes, my wife.

1131
01:41:03,520 --> 01:41:04,520
Mother.

1132
01:41:05,280 --> 01:41:06,360
Yes, my wife.

1133
01:41:10,440 --> 01:41:11,760
Mother, the room is small.

1134
01:41:12,680 --> 01:41:16,280
And now there are two of us.

1135
01:41:16,640 --> 01:41:17,640
That is why.

1136
01:41:18,440 --> 01:41:20,120
We are married.

1137
01:41:20,960 --> 01:41:22,600
My sister.

1138
01:41:23,360 --> 01:41:25,880
Çiçek, the early bird gets the worm.

1139
01:41:26,960 --> 01:41:29,360
Since I married first, the big room…

1140
01:41:30,040 --> 01:41:31,760
belongs to me now.

1141
01:41:32,760 --> 01:41:34,600
Who puts these ideas in your head?

1142
01:41:36,520 --> 01:41:40,039
Is it that woman you married?

1143
01:41:40,040 --> 01:41:41,800
Çiçek, she is your sister in law.

1144
01:41:42,200 --> 01:41:43,200
Enough.

1145
01:41:45,120 --> 01:41:47,000
Berat, lower your voice.

1146
01:41:48,600 --> 01:41:49,920
You turned into bandits.

1147
01:41:50,520 --> 01:41:51,520
That will not happen.

1148
01:41:51,680 --> 01:41:52,920
No one is moving.

1149
01:41:53,400 --> 01:41:55,640
The old order stays. Çiçek keeps her room.

1150
01:41:55,920 --> 01:41:56,920
Do you understand?

1151
01:41:57,280 --> 01:42:00,360
You do not come from the mountains
and drive out the owner of the vineyard.

1152
01:42:10,640 --> 01:42:11,640
Move.

1153
01:42:12,280 --> 01:42:13,720
All right. We did not eat your room.

1154
01:42:19,640 --> 01:42:21,360
Patience.

1155
01:42:21,880 --> 01:42:23,000
Come on, Çiçek.

1156
01:42:30,480 --> 01:42:31,480
My wife.

1157
01:42:31,680 --> 01:42:33,880
I will buy you palaces. What
do you need that room for?

1158
01:42:34,840 --> 01:42:35,840
All right?

1159
01:42:38,200 --> 01:42:39,280
Stop.

1160
01:43:05,720 --> 01:43:08,160
It is cold. Are you cold?

1161
01:43:08,280 --> 01:43:09,280
No.

1162
01:43:09,800 --> 01:43:10,800
Please stop.

1163
01:43:11,920 --> 01:43:12,920
Are you cold?

1164
01:43:14,080 --> 01:43:15,080
I do not get cold.

1165
01:43:16,080 --> 01:43:18,960
You said you were cold
when you had a fever.

1166
01:43:20,840 --> 01:43:22,680
Could it be because you
washed with icy water?

1167
01:43:24,040 --> 01:43:26,280
I probably did it because you had a fever.

1168
01:43:27,880 --> 01:43:29,600
And I took revenge using that excuse.

1169
01:43:32,280 --> 01:43:34,120
So you took advantage of my illness.

1170
01:43:35,680 --> 01:43:37,720
Your fever would not go
down. What else could I do?

1171
01:43:43,720 --> 01:43:44,720
How is your arm?

1172
01:43:45,880 --> 01:43:48,800
Fine. It was only a scratch.

1173
01:43:51,960 --> 01:43:55,000
How did I do such a thing?

1174
01:43:56,320 --> 01:43:58,200
I feel sick just thinking about it.

1175
01:44:02,880 --> 01:44:04,400
What if something had happened to you?

1176
01:44:07,000 --> 01:44:08,360
But it did not.

1177
01:44:11,320 --> 01:44:12,600
You only caused a wound.

1178
01:44:15,640 --> 01:44:16,720
It will never heal.

1179
01:44:18,160 --> 01:44:19,160
Do not say that.

1180
01:44:21,760 --> 01:44:24,080
You provoked me.

1181
01:44:25,840 --> 01:44:27,280
Who pushes someone to hit them?

1182
01:44:28,360 --> 01:44:30,280
You were eager to hit too.

1183
01:44:30,880 --> 01:44:33,280
You insisted on opening
the door. We were fine.

1184
01:44:34,320 --> 01:44:35,320
You were stubborn.

1185
01:44:36,080 --> 01:44:37,280
Listen to you talking.

1186
01:44:38,080 --> 01:44:40,400
As if you are any less stubborn.

1187
01:44:41,160 --> 01:44:42,200
Stubborn Tahir.

1188
01:44:43,720 --> 01:44:46,240
Said stubborn Mercan.

1189
01:44:51,200 --> 01:44:53,280
Let us see which one of
us will fall off the bridge.

1190
01:45:01,760 --> 01:45:03,280
I will not let you fall.

1191
01:45:13,720 --> 01:45:15,160
Coming here was good.

1192
01:45:17,000 --> 01:45:19,480
Getting away from the mansion helped.

1193
01:45:20,960 --> 01:45:24,240
Until yesterday, I thought
I would never laugh again.

1194
01:45:25,800 --> 01:45:27,280
But today is different.

1195
01:45:37,480 --> 01:45:40,240
You will get better every day.

1196
01:45:44,000 --> 01:45:45,400
I will make it up to you.

1197
01:45:47,000 --> 01:45:48,080
You will not get rid of me.

1198
01:45:50,800 --> 01:45:52,960
I do not want to get rid of you.

1199
01:45:58,840 --> 01:45:59,880
Yours looks better.

1200
01:46:00,640 --> 01:46:03,120
But that one is mine. Give me my simit.

1201
01:47:09,480 --> 01:47:10,960
Your arm is injured.

1202
01:47:11,600 --> 01:47:12,680
Be careful.

1203
01:47:55,320 --> 01:47:56,600
Welcome.

1204
01:47:56,960 --> 01:47:57,960
Thank you.

1205
01:47:59,080 --> 01:48:00,440
How are things at the mansion?

1206
01:48:00,960 --> 01:48:02,880
Nothing changed. Same as you left it.

1207
01:48:04,600 --> 01:48:06,480
I came to see Mercan.

1208
01:48:06,920 --> 01:48:09,760
So many secrets and lies came out.

1209
01:48:11,080 --> 01:48:12,320
The poor girl is devastated.

1210
01:48:13,080 --> 01:48:14,080
They went out.

1211
01:48:15,880 --> 01:48:17,440
I know. I spoke to them.

1212
01:48:19,000 --> 01:48:20,280
It is good they went out.

1213
01:48:21,480 --> 01:48:23,680
They are trying to heal their wounds.

1214
01:48:24,280 --> 01:48:25,280
I cannot blame them.

1215
01:48:28,120 --> 01:48:30,720
Ateş cannot bear seeing Mercan sad.

1216
01:48:31,200 --> 01:48:32,200
He loves her deeply.

1217
01:48:33,280 --> 01:48:34,360
Mercan feels the same.

1218
01:48:35,560 --> 01:48:38,880
When she hears Ateş’s
name, her eyes change.

1219
01:48:49,040 --> 01:48:50,680
Love forgives everything.

1220
01:48:52,200 --> 01:48:54,560
Insallah. They went through hard times.

1221
01:48:54,800 --> 01:48:56,320
Neither of them deserved this.

1222
01:48:57,240 --> 01:48:58,240
Yes.

1223
01:48:59,480 --> 01:49:04,720
Love wounds, but it heals too.

1224
01:49:06,000 --> 01:49:07,760
Then can we say this?

1225
01:49:08,080 --> 01:49:09,480
May their love heal them both.

1226
01:49:21,280 --> 01:49:25,040
I will wait on the veranda
until Mercan arrives.

1227
01:49:25,480 --> 01:49:27,440
All right. I will send
you tea. Drink it slowly.

1228
01:49:28,000 --> 01:49:29,440
All right. Thank you.

1229
01:49:53,880 --> 01:49:54,880
Welcome, my Çiçek.

1230
01:49:56,400 --> 01:49:57,760
It is not a welcome at all.

1231
01:49:59,240 --> 01:50:02,840
Why? What happened?

1232
01:50:03,640 --> 01:50:05,920
That witch Zehra gets on my nerves.

1233
01:50:06,160 --> 01:50:09,320
And my brother watches
her like a fool in love.

1234
01:50:11,600 --> 01:50:13,640
You live in the same
house. That is expected.

1235
01:50:14,200 --> 01:50:15,640
But we need a solution.

1236
01:50:15,920 --> 01:50:18,080
We will face each other
every day. This will not work.

1237
01:50:18,920 --> 01:50:23,240
Forget this nonsense. Why did you call me?

1238
01:50:24,800 --> 01:50:25,800
I bought a ticket.

1239
01:50:26,880 --> 01:50:28,320
I fly to Cairo in two days.

1240
01:50:29,120 --> 01:50:30,800
I am so excited.

1241
01:50:31,240 --> 01:50:31,760
Me too.

1242
01:50:32,160 --> 01:50:34,199
Insallah you return with good news.

1243
01:50:34,200 --> 01:50:37,440
This trip will pave
the way to our happiness.

1244
01:50:38,760 --> 01:50:40,680
I know. I trust you.

1245
01:50:40,720 --> 01:50:43,160
May you go like the wind and
return like a flood, Insallah.

1246
01:50:44,160 --> 01:50:45,320
Of course I will return.

1247
01:50:46,320 --> 01:50:47,600
Of course.

1248
01:50:49,320 --> 01:50:52,400
Because I cannot endure without seeing you.

1249
01:50:55,640 --> 01:50:56,920
I need to see you all the time.

1250
01:50:59,560 --> 01:51:03,160
My parents are waiting. I must go.

1251
01:51:04,400 --> 01:51:08,320
All right. Go. We will talk later.

1252
01:51:25,360 --> 01:51:26,480
What the hell is going on?

1253
01:51:29,320 --> 01:51:30,440
Malik, calm down.

1254
01:51:46,240 --> 01:51:47,400
The sea air helped.

1255
01:51:48,720 --> 01:51:50,000
It smells of the sea.

1256
01:51:51,120 --> 01:51:53,360
If the weather stays nice,
we will go out by boat.

1257
01:51:57,560 --> 01:51:58,840
I will check on Demet.

1258
01:51:59,360 --> 01:52:00,360
All right.

1259
01:52:16,560 --> 01:52:18,600
My dear, how are you?

1260
01:52:25,920 --> 01:52:26,920
How do you think I am?

1261
01:52:28,000 --> 01:52:29,640
This burden is too heavy.

1262
01:52:31,560 --> 01:52:33,080
I try to be fine.

1263
01:52:36,720 --> 01:52:39,040
But I cannot stop thinking about Eylül.

1264
01:52:41,520 --> 01:52:45,080
My heart burns when I think of her.

1265
01:52:47,480 --> 01:52:48,480
You are right.

1266
01:52:49,640 --> 01:52:51,480
You went through heavy things.

1267
01:52:52,800 --> 01:52:53,960
How are you and Ateş?

1268
01:52:56,040 --> 01:52:57,440
I want to be angry at him.

1269
01:52:58,760 --> 01:53:00,600
I want to hurt him.

1270
01:53:03,240 --> 01:53:09,040
I say I will never
forgive him for the lies.

1271
01:53:11,280 --> 01:53:15,080
But when I look into his
eyes… my heart races…

1272
01:53:16,080 --> 01:53:17,440
everything goes silent.

1273
01:53:21,280 --> 01:53:23,680
That great anger shatters.

1274
01:53:25,520 --> 01:53:27,080
Only love remains.

1275
01:53:30,880 --> 01:53:32,880
We spent such a beautiful morning…

1276
01:53:33,720 --> 01:53:35,400
I had so much fun.

1277
01:53:37,280 --> 01:53:38,960
With him, I forget everything.

1278
01:53:41,760 --> 01:53:43,480
Then I get angry at myself.

1279
01:53:44,640 --> 01:53:46,520
Even after all the pain he caused…

1280
01:53:46,760 --> 01:53:49,480
I still feel this way.

1281
01:53:51,440 --> 01:53:52,440
My struggle never ends.

1282
01:53:53,360 --> 01:53:54,960
I do not know which will win.

1283
01:53:56,480 --> 01:53:59,000
My love or my anger.

1284
01:54:01,400 --> 01:54:04,800
Then I remember what my father did to him.

1285
01:54:05,840 --> 01:54:06,840
My heart melts.

1286
01:54:08,400 --> 01:54:09,600
I lose to love.

1287
01:54:28,760 --> 01:54:31,320
Here. A sibling’s share.

1288
01:54:31,880 --> 01:54:32,880
For healing.

1289
01:54:38,000 --> 01:54:39,680
You keep walking in the garden these days.

1290
01:54:40,360 --> 01:54:41,600
The weather got cold.

1291
01:54:42,120 --> 01:54:44,640
It can put even a tough
young man in bed. Be careful.

1292
01:54:50,280 --> 01:54:51,280
Mercan loves it too.

1293
01:54:55,240 --> 01:54:56,600
Loved it.

1294
01:54:58,520 --> 01:54:59,520
As a child.

1295
01:55:01,720 --> 01:55:04,560
She took many blows.

1296
01:55:07,240 --> 01:55:08,440
From her family, from me.

1297
01:55:10,800 --> 01:55:12,640
Yet she endures.

1298
01:55:14,480 --> 01:55:16,200
She smiles, but sadness stays in her eyes.

1299
01:55:18,240 --> 01:55:20,400
It will pass. That too will pass.

1300
01:55:21,040 --> 01:55:22,360
Mercan lived through hard things.

1301
01:55:24,600 --> 01:55:27,520
If you want to stand by
her, you must stay strong.

1302
01:55:28,800 --> 01:55:30,680
Be patient a little longer.

1303
01:55:31,880 --> 01:55:33,000
Time will heal Mercan.

1304
01:55:37,200 --> 01:55:38,320
It hurts so much.

1305
01:55:39,960 --> 01:55:42,280
I never felt this helpless.

1306
01:55:45,200 --> 01:55:49,840
The most innocent suffers the most.

1307
01:55:51,400 --> 01:55:55,000
In this life with all its ups
and downs, I learned one thing.

1308
01:55:57,880 --> 01:55:59,520
The innocent usually take the first blow.

1309
01:56:01,480 --> 01:56:03,880
But they are also the first to be rewarded.

1310
01:56:05,400 --> 01:56:06,480
Mercan is innocent.

1311
01:56:07,360 --> 01:56:08,960
Yes, she lived through hard things, but…

1312
01:56:09,560 --> 01:56:11,840
I am sure she will soon face life.

1313
01:56:15,400 --> 01:56:16,400
I hope so.

1314
01:56:17,400 --> 01:56:18,560
It will happen. Do not worry.

1315
01:56:32,160 --> 01:56:35,480
Thank you. You are always by my side.

1316
01:56:35,760 --> 01:56:37,680
I will always be by your side.

1317
01:56:45,000 --> 01:56:46,000
Brother?

1318
01:56:46,520 --> 01:56:49,160
Get in the car and wait. I am coming.

1319
01:56:53,880 --> 01:56:54,880
Can we talk a little?

1320
01:56:56,080 --> 01:56:57,080
About what?

1321
01:56:57,720 --> 01:56:58,760
About Ateş.

1322
01:57:01,640 --> 01:57:03,600
I learned you locked your
father in the basement.

1323
01:57:04,080 --> 01:57:05,880
This man has completely lost it, Mercan.

1324
01:57:08,960 --> 01:57:11,720
I am worried about you. About your family.

1325
01:57:13,520 --> 01:57:14,880
I said it before.

1326
01:57:15,400 --> 01:57:17,240
Say the word and I will
deal with that bandit.

1327
01:57:17,400 --> 01:57:18,480
What do you mean by that?

1328
01:57:18,920 --> 01:57:19,320
Mercan.

1329
01:57:19,400 --> 01:57:20,800
Look, Nezir.

1330
01:57:21,920 --> 01:57:23,000
I warned you before.

1331
01:57:24,960 --> 01:57:26,000
I warn you again.

1332
01:57:26,720 --> 01:57:28,320
Do not come to me with this.

1333
01:57:29,360 --> 01:57:32,320
You accuse Ateş of being a bandit.

1334
01:57:33,360 --> 01:57:34,880
Then what does that make you?

1335
01:57:36,680 --> 01:57:37,680
Just.

1336
01:57:40,520 --> 01:57:41,520
Just.

1337
01:57:42,040 --> 01:57:44,280
You have to speak to him in
the language he understands.

1338
01:57:45,360 --> 01:57:47,400
That makes me just, not a bandit.

1339
01:57:48,760 --> 01:57:50,960
I beg you, think again.

1340
01:57:54,000 --> 01:57:55,760
I told you before.

1341
01:57:57,360 --> 01:57:58,640
I say it for the last time.

1342
01:58:00,400 --> 01:58:03,120
Every harm you do to
Ateş, I take as done to me.

1343
01:58:06,280 --> 01:58:08,400
When he hurts, I hurt.

1344
01:58:11,800 --> 01:58:14,920
If you harm Ateş, you will face me.

1345
01:58:17,920 --> 01:58:21,400
If I were you, I would stay away from him.

1346
01:58:48,520 --> 01:58:50,280
We just came back. Where are you going?

1347
01:58:51,920 --> 01:58:54,080
There is a place I want to go.

1348
01:58:54,600 --> 01:58:56,560
Then let us go together.

1349
01:58:57,280 --> 01:58:59,520
It is better if I go alone. Please.

1350
01:59:00,480 --> 01:59:02,480
All right.

1351
01:59:06,520 --> 01:59:08,440
We will look at each other like before.

1352
01:59:12,040 --> 01:59:13,040
With love.

1353
01:59:14,440 --> 01:59:15,720
Far from pain.

1354
01:59:18,480 --> 01:59:19,720
Only with love.

1355
01:59:23,120 --> 01:59:25,440
There is a war between
your mind and your heart.

1356
01:59:27,360 --> 01:59:28,760
I know that war well.

1357
01:59:31,360 --> 01:59:31,840
I…

1358
01:59:31,841 --> 01:59:33,960
I resisted my feelings at first.

1359
01:59:36,600 --> 01:59:39,640
I tried to run, ignored them, denied them.

1360
01:59:42,640 --> 01:59:45,160
But I failed.

1361
01:59:50,080 --> 01:59:51,440
In the end, I lost to my heart.

1362
01:59:54,320 --> 01:59:56,600
Now it rules me.

1363
02:00:00,240 --> 02:00:02,320
I am no different from you.

1364
02:00:08,200 --> 02:00:09,200
I lose to my heart.

1365
02:00:12,040 --> 02:00:16,440
But my disappointment is so great.

1366
02:00:17,640 --> 02:00:20,000
So alive.

1367
02:00:21,640 --> 02:00:24,080
Sometimes it drowns out my heart.

1368
02:00:27,640 --> 02:00:29,120
I cannot blame you for this.

1369
02:00:42,320 --> 02:00:43,360
But know this.

1370
02:00:46,680 --> 02:00:51,760
Whether you forgive or not,
I will not give up on you.

1371
02:00:54,840 --> 02:00:56,080
I will wait for you.

1372
02:01:24,800 --> 02:01:27,160
Mr. Haydar wants to see you.

1373
02:01:28,320 --> 02:01:29,040
What does he want?

1374
02:01:29,320 --> 02:01:32,280
I do not know. He said it was important.

1375
02:01:50,080 --> 02:01:52,200
We will skin this one alive.

1376
02:01:52,320 --> 02:01:53,320
We will put it here.

1377
02:01:53,920 --> 02:01:55,000
Are you ready, my daughter?

1378
02:01:55,440 --> 02:01:57,720
Ready, mother. I am sending it now.

1379
02:01:58,200 --> 02:01:59,200
Bring it.
Here.

1380
02:02:07,480 --> 02:02:09,600
Mother, well done. It looks great.

1381
02:02:10,160 --> 02:02:11,600
Enjoy your meal, my son.

1382
02:02:12,000 --> 02:02:13,520
Let it be plenty and nourishing.

1383
02:02:14,640 --> 02:02:16,800
Someone would think my brother is weak.

1384
02:02:16,880 --> 02:02:18,560
Look at him. He looks strong.

1385
02:02:20,520 --> 02:02:21,760
Strength comes from the throat.

1386
02:02:21,960 --> 02:02:23,160
And leaves from there too.

1387
02:02:23,240 --> 02:02:24,640
Still, be careful.

1388
02:02:27,280 --> 02:02:29,000
My wife, would you like to taste it too?

1389
02:02:30,040 --> 02:02:31,520
Did they leave me any appetite?

1390
02:02:46,320 --> 02:02:47,320
Is this how it works?

1391
02:02:48,280 --> 02:02:49,480
All right. Continue like this.

1392
02:02:50,480 --> 02:02:52,680
That Tahir is a good boy.

1393
02:02:54,440 --> 02:02:57,760
He came to the kitchen,
kissed my hand, hugged me.

1394
02:02:58,240 --> 02:02:59,680
We talked about old days.

1395
02:03:02,160 --> 02:03:03,280
Those days.

1396
02:03:07,000 --> 02:03:09,360
Something bothers me, mother.

1397
02:03:10,040 --> 02:03:11,640
How will we address this man?

1398
02:03:12,120 --> 02:03:14,999
Mr. Ateş or Mr. Tahir?

1399
02:03:15,000 --> 02:03:19,280
We should ask him.

1400
02:03:20,160 --> 02:03:21,160
You are right.

1401
02:03:26,480 --> 02:03:27,840
What is this?

1402
02:03:28,280 --> 02:03:29,640
It came for Malik.

1403
02:03:32,560 --> 02:03:34,880
It looks like an official document.

1404
02:03:36,600 --> 02:03:37,720
Strange.

1405
02:03:39,720 --> 02:03:40,720
Good luck.

1406
02:03:40,800 --> 02:03:42,800
Malik, this is for you.

1407
02:03:43,040 --> 02:03:43,680
For me?

1408
02:03:43,681 --> 02:03:46,720
I was about to open it when you came.

1409
02:03:46,880 --> 02:03:47,880
Who sent it?

1410
02:03:50,200 --> 02:03:51,200
I do not know.

1411
02:03:59,840 --> 02:04:01,280
It came from the immigration office.

1412
02:04:04,840 --> 02:04:06,000
What is it, my son?

1413
02:04:08,920 --> 02:04:09,960
What happened?

1414
02:04:11,320 --> 02:04:13,240
My residence permit was rejected.

1415
02:04:19,640 --> 02:04:21,040
They will deport me.

1416
02:04:24,400 --> 02:04:25,400
What?

1417
02:04:47,920 --> 02:04:48,920
Ateş.

1418
02:04:49,200 --> 02:04:50,720
Ateş, enough. Get me out of here.

1419
02:04:51,280 --> 02:04:53,200
Ateş, get me out of
here. Do you not hear me?

1420
02:04:54,120 --> 02:04:55,120
Ateş.

1421
02:05:01,720 --> 02:05:02,720
What do you want?

1422
02:05:04,080 --> 02:05:06,040
I cannot stand it anymore.
I am suffocating here.

1423
02:05:06,080 --> 02:05:07,080
Get me out of here.

1424
02:05:08,320 --> 02:05:10,360
Where you could not last one day…

1425
02:05:11,080 --> 02:05:14,000
I stayed 187 days with Eylül.

1426
02:05:16,200 --> 02:05:19,080
If we endured it, you will too.

1427
02:05:22,560 --> 02:05:23,560
Now shut up and sit.

1428
02:05:28,680 --> 02:05:30,240
How is Mercan? Is she well?

1429
02:05:30,600 --> 02:05:31,880
Do not say her name.

1430
02:05:33,560 --> 02:05:34,960
Do not pretend to care.

1431
02:05:36,320 --> 02:05:38,480
No one hurt Mercan as much as you did.

1432
02:05:41,600 --> 02:05:42,920
And you call yourself her father.

1433
02:05:43,760 --> 02:05:48,360
You are the lowest man I know.

1434
02:05:52,760 --> 02:05:53,760
No.

1435
02:05:54,920 --> 02:05:55,360
Do not.

1436
02:05:55,840 --> 02:05:57,720
Do not try this again.

1437
02:05:59,520 --> 02:06:01,240
You do not know the truth about Eylül.

1438
02:06:01,840 --> 02:06:03,320
If you did, you would understand me.

1439
02:06:03,960 --> 02:06:05,480
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

1440
02:06:06,200 --> 02:06:07,200
I did not kill her.

1441
02:06:08,560 --> 02:06:10,520
How many times will
you repeat the same lie?

1442
02:06:11,280 --> 02:06:14,400
There are many things you do
not know, but now you must learn.

1443
02:06:15,560 --> 02:06:16,560
What do you mean?

1444
02:06:17,600 --> 02:06:19,120
Are you ready to hear the truth?

1445
02:06:20,000 --> 02:06:21,960
Speak clearly.

1446
02:06:24,200 --> 02:06:27,280
Did you never wonder
why and how Eylül died?

1447
02:06:31,840 --> 02:06:33,440
Speak or I will kill you.

1448
02:07:11,880 --> 02:07:15,800
There are many things you do
not know, but now you must learn.

1449
02:07:18,480 --> 02:07:21,560
Did you never wonder
why and how Eylül died?

1450
02:07:42,000 --> 02:07:43,000
Eylül.

1451
02:07:44,920 --> 02:07:48,640
Believing your tiny body lies here…

1452
02:07:55,640 --> 02:07:58,960
accepting the truth is so hard.

1453
02:08:02,320 --> 02:08:04,240
Like a flower that withered too soon…

1454
02:08:05,320 --> 02:08:07,800
you fell to the earth early.

1455
02:08:13,520 --> 02:08:16,320
You should have lived.

1456
02:08:21,760 --> 02:08:26,320
You should have grown, loved, been loved.

1457
02:08:29,400 --> 02:08:31,120
You should have tasted life.

1458
02:08:42,560 --> 02:08:44,279
I am ashamed of myself…

1459
02:08:44,280 --> 02:08:47,800
for being the daughter of
the man who caused your death.

1460
02:08:50,920 --> 02:08:55,160
I was only a child.

1461
02:08:56,640 --> 02:09:00,440
I do not know what I could
have done, but I wish I had seen.

1462
02:09:00,800 --> 02:09:02,360
I wish I had noticed.

1463
02:09:03,320 --> 02:09:06,520
I wish I had helped you.

1464
02:09:07,760 --> 02:09:10,040
I am so sorry.

1465
02:09:25,480 --> 02:09:28,800
All right. I will tell you. Lower the gun.

1466
02:09:29,000 --> 02:09:30,000
I will speak.

1467
02:09:32,280 --> 02:09:33,280
I will tell everything.

1468
02:09:37,600 --> 02:09:39,600
That day, I took Eylül away.

1469
02:09:40,520 --> 02:09:41,840
We were going to take her kidney.

1470
02:09:44,040 --> 02:09:45,040
What?

1471
02:09:45,760 --> 02:09:47,200
I will kill you.

1472
02:09:47,720 --> 02:09:49,040
What are you saying?

1473
02:09:49,360 --> 02:09:50,480
I am telling the truth.

1474
02:09:50,920 --> 02:09:51,920
No.

1475
02:09:52,000 --> 02:09:53,560
You are trying to die.

1476
02:09:54,120 --> 02:09:55,320
Death is your salvation.

1477
02:09:55,520 --> 02:09:56,800
Do you still not understand?

1478
02:09:57,600 --> 02:09:59,840
Mercan had kidney disease.

1479
02:10:03,760 --> 02:10:05,200
Without a transplant, she would die.

1480
02:10:10,520 --> 02:10:12,200
She was the only compatible donor.

1481
02:10:14,480 --> 02:10:16,560
I did everything for my daughter.

1482
02:10:16,760 --> 02:10:18,200
I have no regret.

1483
02:10:19,400 --> 02:10:20,400
No.

1484
02:10:27,160 --> 02:10:35,160
No. No. No.

1485
02:10:38,000 --> 02:10:39,000
This is not true, is it?

1486
02:10:40,440 --> 02:10:41,920
Every word is true.

1487
02:10:47,800 --> 02:10:50,320
For Mercan to live, Eylül had to die.

1488
02:10:55,800 --> 02:10:58,560
If I faced the same choice
again today, I would do the same.

1489
02:11:10,680 --> 02:11:12,080
I chose my daughter.

1490
02:11:16,320 --> 02:11:17,400
Tell me, Ateş.

1491
02:11:17,840 --> 02:11:21,560
To save the one you love,
would you take another life?

1492
02:11:36,720 --> 02:11:39,160
For Mercan to live, Eylül had to die.

1493
02:13:43,840 --> 02:13:45,440
You said that you had known how to fish.

1494
02:13:46,880 --> 02:13:48,080
But it doesn't seem like this.

1495
02:13:48,520 --> 02:13:49,600
Why sis you say this?

1496
02:13:50,760 --> 02:13:51,760
I know.

1497
02:13:56,880 --> 02:13:57,880
I caught a fish.

1498
02:13:59,160 --> 02:14:00,160
I did, did you see?

1499
02:14:00,800 --> 02:14:02,440
You couldn't but I did.

1500
02:14:07,160 --> 02:14:08,160
It doesn't come.

1501
02:14:11,320 --> 02:14:12,320
Let me help you.

1502
02:14:38,680 --> 02:14:39,680
It pulls.

1503
02:14:40,800 --> 02:14:41,800
Hold tight.

1504
02:15:52,960 --> 02:15:54,240
Come on.
